title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield 1911 with Wilson Combat Upgrades
postcontent:
This is an extremely nice Springfield Armory 1911-A1 Tactical/Comp .45 ACP manufactured about 1989 with a “NM” prefix serial number. It has been enhanced with several $$$ added features. Springfield built this gun on a Springfield Series 70 frame and slide.

It has been Enhanced with a Wilson Combat (match) threaded barrel. It shows an attached screw on compensator (also takes a suppressor or just a knurled thread protector) and a Wilson fitted bushing & link. Has S.S. Mag well, Target grips, Wilson Extended takedown and ambidextrous safety and an extended mag release button. Also has the Wilson two piece solid guide rod with spring and reverse rod holder.

This gun with the enhanced trigger group including combat hammer, has as nice of a trigger pull on it, as guns costing twice as much as I'm asking. I believe the series 70 frame and slide has something to do with that as well.

Slide and frame fit like a glove, and move as smooth as glass together, with no play or hesitation at all, and makes the gun much more accurate than I am as a shooter. I would consider the overall finish as 98%+.

If you are looking for an easy shooting (reduced recoil when using the  compensator) .45 for pleasure, tactical use, or to possibly get into a little competition without a lot of investment, then this is the 1911 for you.

I already have (5) other .45's so I decided to sell this little treasure to someone that can do it justice.

title: For Sale:  Noreen
postcontent:
I also take trades like hunting rifles, tactical rifles, handguns and quality optics. Just email me directly at sales@darcopsarmory.com and tell me what you have. Maybe we can work out a trade or use it as a partial down payment.

WE DO SHIP TO CALIFORNIA! It is up to you, the buyer, to make sure this is legal in your area, and if it is we are an approved seller to the state of California and are more than happy to serve you.

We are an FFL and will accept trade-ins, shipped to us or brought in locally, from individuals. No need to pay your FFL a fee for doing it when we can walk you through the process.

I also set up payment plans on expensive items like this one so just email me and let me know what down payment and monthly payment you can afford and maybe we can put it on lay-a-way for you.

This item is new, we are a licensed gun shop and we received it from the manufacturer or a distributor. It has never been fired and since our shop specializes in more expensive, higher end merchandise we are not open to the public. This usually means you will get a pristine, mint condition example that has never been handled by anybody as most of our inventory is received and shipped out in the same box it arrived in and never even opened.

NOREEN BAD NEWS .300 WIN MAG !!!!

Noreen has created the ONLY SEMI-AUTOMATIC .300 WIN MAG and .338 Lapua on the market. The BAD NEWS is a custom-made AR-style rifle that is chambered in the increasingly popular 338 Lapua as well as the powerful 300 WIN MAG. These cartridges give you much greater velocity and power than the typical .308, and as far as ballistics are concerned, the BAD NEWS rifle is going to be the flatter shooting gun for long range shots.

The BAD NEWS rifle is a piston-driven semi-auto; this means you can expect greater range and a higher level of reliability by running a cleaner and cooler rifle. The muzzle break on these Noreen’s significantly suppresses recoil. Additionally, the semi-auto nature of the rifle will naturally recoil less than a bolt action because part of the felt recoil is going to chamber the next round. Lighter recoil is a huge advantage when you’re looking for a rifle with a faster and more accurate follow-up shot.

This piston-driven system is unlike any other AR-10 on the market. The piston movement is strictly in the action, after the bullet has already left the barrel. This is a huge advantage on a precision rifle compared to conventional piston driven setups found in standard AR's. In those rifles, an LWRC REPR, POF P308, etc. the piston runs parallel to the barrel and moves while the bullet is still in the barrel creating unwanted barrel harmonics which adversely affect accuracy. This rifle's piston is located in the receiver and not along the barrel so the bullet is out of the barrel by the time the piston is working to chamber another round and keep your action cool and clean with no gas ever entering the action.

The semi-automatic will not only give you a much faster follow-up shot, it also allows you to stay focused on your target, optic and the trigger, instead of having to manually operate a bolt-action rifle; all subsequent rounds are chambered by the rifle itself during the gas or blowback operation of the action.

The weapon easily disassembles like the standard AR for quick and easy cleaning and reassembly. The piston system drastically reduces fouling, and no venting means no holes for dirt and other contaminants to enter the system.

The full-length Picatinny rail on the receiver will allow you to mount scopes, lights, lasers, bipods, bayonets, etc. The adjustable cheek rest stock option is an added upgrade free bonus.

This item is new, we are a licensed gun shop and we received it from the manufacturer or a distributor. It has never been fired and since our shop specializes in more expensive, higher end merchandise we are not open to the public. This usually means you will get a pristine, mint condition example that has never been handled by anybody as most of our inventory is received and shipped out in the same box it arrived in and never even opened.

NOREEN BAD NEWS .300 WIN MAG !!!!

Noreen has created the ONLY SEMI-AUTOMATIC .300 WIN MAG and .338 Lapua on the market. The BAD NEWS is a custom-made AR-style rifle that is chambered in the increasingly popular 338 Lapua as well as the powerful 300 WIN MAG. These cartridges give you much greater velocity and power than the typical .308, and as far as ballistics are concerned, the BAD NEWS rifle is going to be the flatter shooting gun for long range shots.

The BAD NEWS rifle is a piston-driven semi-auto; this means you can expect greater range and a higher level of reliability by running a cleaner and cooler rifle. The muzzle break on these Noreen’s significantly suppresses recoil. Additionally, the semi-auto nature of the rifle will naturally recoil less than a bolt action because part of the felt recoil is going to chamber the next round. Lighter recoil is a huge advantage when you’re looking for a rifle with a faster and more accurate follow-up shot.

This piston-driven system is unlike any other AR-10 on the market. The piston movement is strictly in the action, after the bullet has already left the barrel. This is a huge advantage on a precision rifle compared to conventional piston driven setups found in standard AR's. In those rifles, an LWRC REPR, POF P308, etc. the piston runs parallel to the barrel and moves while the bullet is still in the barrel creating unwanted barrel harmonics which adversely affect accuracy. This rifle's piston is located in the receiver and not along the barrel so the bullet is out of the barrel by the time the piston is working to chamber another round and keep your action cool and clean with no gas ever entering the action.

The semi-automatic will not only give you a much faster follow-up shot, it also allows you to stay focused on your target, optic and the trigger, instead of having to manually operate a bolt-action rifle; all subsequent rounds are chambered by the rifle itself during the gas or blowback operation of the action.

The weapon easily disassembles like the standard AR for quick and easy cleaning and reassembly. The piston system drastically reduces fouling, and no venting means no holes for dirt and other contaminants to enter the system.

postcontent:
This is Smith and Wesson's first version of the Peformance Center on the AR15 Platform. It is top quality through and through. This Smith & Wesson's M&P 15PC-1 from the Performance Center is one of the top choice for any serious shooter, and very hard to find. This earlier model is superior than the current model on the receiver and stock. This S&W Performance Center M&P 15PC-1 has a 20” Stainless Steel barrel, Chromed Bolt Carrier, Two-Stage compitition trigger, Hard Coat black anodized finish from the factory.

I use this rifle for hunting coyote sometimes, but mostly use it for varmit (Despite what Obama says about people using AR's for hunting), It has earned such nickname's as the "Black Death" and "Nail Driver" amongst my friends. The accuracy is second to none, it is almost boring to shoot because I can hold a dime size group at 100 yards all day with it. So unless you're using it to shoot 2-3" targets at 150-200 yards it's boring at the range lol. 

I am a U.S. Marine so needless to say the weapon has been well taken care of. It is in peak condition mechanically, but shows signs of use. As I said, I have not bought it to sit in a safe and collect dust, I bought it to be a deadly accurate weapon system, and that it is. If you're looking for a unfired weapon or a weapon to sit in a safe and collect dust then please move on because this is not what you're looking for. However, if you're looking for a field tested and true'd weapon, that has this U.S. Marine's approval; this is it. 

Now to the price... When the weapon hit the market the MSRP was $2750 for the bare rifle. That means no optics and no bipod.

title: For Sale:  HK MR556 AR15 M4 5.56 .223 NT COLT LWRC 223 NIB
postcontent:
Manufacturer: 	 Heckler & Koch
Model: 	         MR556
Caliber: 	         5.56mm NATO
Barrel Length: 	 16 inch
Capacity: 	         30-39

Up for auction is the mr556a1, A direct descendent of the HK416. The MR556A1 is a semi-automatic rifle developed by Heckler & Koch as a premium level commercial/civilian firearm with match rifle capability. Like the HK416, the MR556A1 is a major product improvement over conventional AR-type carbines and rifles. The MR556A1 uses the HK proprietary gas piston operating system, employing a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms. This method of operation virtually eliminates malfunctions that are common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. This is the same key feature critical to the success of the HK416 rifles used by leading military and law enforcement customers. The MR556A1 is produced in the USA using American and German made components. The MR556A1 uses many of the same assemblies and accessories originally developed for the HK416 including the HK free-floating four-quadrant rail system. The HK Free Floating Rail System (FFRS) handguard has four MIL-STD-1913 “Picatinny” rails and allows all current accessories, sights, lights, and aimers used on M4/M16-type arms to be fitted to the MR Series. The HK rail system can be installed and removed with simple tools and returns to zero when reinstalled. The MR556A1 also has a Picantinny rail machined into the top of its upper receiver for mounting optics and mechanical sights. Unlike earlier prototypes, major subassemblies, including the MR556A1 upper receiver/barrel assembly, are fully interchangeable with other high quality AR-style firearms. MR556A1 upper receiver kits can be used to retrofit competing legacy AR systems. Like the famous HK416, the MR556A1 uses a German-made barrel produced by Heckler & Koch’s famous cold hammer forging process. The highest quality steel is used in this unique manufacturing process producing a barrel that provides superior accuracy and long service life. But unlike the HK416, the MR556A1 does not use a chrome-lined barrel. Chrome-lining can sometimes mask bore imperfections and negatively affect accuracy. For the new series of Heckler & Koch semi-automatic MR rifles, HK designers and engineers believe best accuracy comes with an unlined bore. Used with the HK Free Floating Rail System, the barrel does not touch the handguard, ensuring the barrel is truly free-floating for maximum accuracy. The unchromed barrel has an internal profile of 6 lands and grooves with a 1 in 7 inch (178 mm) twist. It is also moderately “swagged” with a slightly smaller internal diameter at the muzzle end than the chamber end. This feature has a positive effect on bullet accuracy and velocity. The thick, heavy contour 16.5-inch MR556A1 barrel also contributes to its excellent accuracy. A precise enhanced two-stage trigger adds significantly to the accuracy of the MR556A1 and an extended latch charging handle makes operating the rifle with a telescopic sight easier. The retractable buttstock can be locked into a solid, non-moving position by tightening an Allen screw in the bottom of the stock. Special target rifle takedown pins ensure the upper and lower receivers are firmly mated for accurate performance. Designed to function with a wide variety of high quality 5.56 x 45 mm ammunition, the MR556A1 uses a C.I.P. dimensioned chamber (a chamber with dimensions specified by the Commission Internationale Permanente).The MR556A1 also functions reliably with most quality Caliber .223 Remington ammunition. The MR556A1 is being produced with the same commitment to quality as German-made HK firearms. By using joint U.S./German manufacturing, Heckler & Koch leverages the relative strengths of two continents to make the preeminent AR-type firearm, combining the designs innovations of the USA and Germany into one new product.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Marlin XL7 .30-06 and Scope 420 rounds and reloading equipment.
postcontent:
Comes with 420 rounds of AMMO. A Lee Classic Loader for 30-06 and a pound of powder, Lee safety scale, bullet puller, and any other reloading equipment I have.
Bolt is very smooth and easy to work on this rifle you would think this .30 OC 6 (7.62×63mm for the metric readers) was a semi-automatic in the right hands. Making for quick accurate shots even at running game. The receiver is made of machined 4140 steel alloy for rigid strength lending to accuracy. Headspace is set with a barrel nut for quick tight headspace setting. And for the ones who like perfection you can easily set the headspace to whatever specification you want. The barrel nut also is easily removed with an easy to get tool, so that you can change out barrels. There are currently several barrels for sale for savage rifles online that are said to be able to fit this rifle. I see a .270 barrel and a 300 mag barrel both at .99 cents on ebay right now. Also there are barrels made specifically for the Marlin available also.

The synthetic stock has steel pillars to maintain a consistent stock/action interface, checkering on grip and fore end with sling studs. Adjustable trigger can easily be set by about anyone with simple tools from hair trigger to next to almost impossible to pull trigger(who would want that I don't know but it is possible). This rifle has a great trigger system very smooth and easy to use for accurate shots. Specially in the heat of the moment it's natural so you can get the kill. 

Has cocking indicator on the bolt so you know when it is cocked and ready to fire. Has grove in the rail to prevent binding and smooth up feeding. Safety is Nickle a common place where sweaty fingers make for rusty parts. The nickle will not rust from the salt from your fingers from lots of use.

This gun is capable of sub .75" accuracy and has room to grow where it could be a sub .25" with the right mods. One thing that could be done easily would be to float the barrel and bed the action or could get an upgraded much more expensive high high end stock that was already modified that way. Personally I would do the work myself if I were to keep the rifle. The rifle at this point is all original and has had very few rounds put threw it. This rifle is in excellent shape and is very clean almost mint shape. Bottom line is this is alot of rifle for the money I have had rifles that costed $2,000 that this rifle would best.

The EMAG is an improved Pmag, a lightweight 30-round 5.56x45 NATO polymer magazine that features a number of aesthetic and functional changes from the PMAG®. The EMAG remains 100% compatible with the AR15/M16 platform, its unique geometry is optimized for use in not only the AR-15 and Colt M16 but also for foreign-made weapons such as the British SA-80 (L85A1/A2, L86A1/A2, L22A1, L98A1/A2), HK 416, M27 IAR. These are packaged in military issue packaging, with NSN identification numbering on the back of the package.
